# Description of Macedonian constellation Thieves
msgid ""
"The famous constellation Ursa Major among the people is described as a group of\n"
"thieves (_Aramii_). The seven bright stars of Ursa Major are said to be thieves\n"
"„because during the entire night they circle on the sky same as thieves that\n"
"circle around houses“"
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Mother Hen
msgid ""
"Mother Hen (_Kvachka_) is the best-known constellation, which is recognized by\n"
"all elderly people in Macedonian villages, without any exception. This name\n"
"people use for the star cluster Pleiades."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Plough
msgid ""
"The constellation Orion with its numerous bright stars and distinctive pattern\n"
"dominates the winter sky and can be easily found. People from Macedonian\n"
"villages usually point at the region around Orion’s belt saying that three\n"
"bright stars and surrounding less bright stars create an image of a wooden\n"
"Plough with two yoked oxen (_Ralo so Volovi_)."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Yoke
msgid ""
"Yoke (_Jarem_). People under this name recognize group of stars in the\n"
"constellation Perseus. Yokes for the oxen usually is found in village yards so\n"
"that is why, like the previous constellation, it is an evidence of the general\n"
"image of people and purpose given to this part of the sky."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Wolves
msgid ""
"Near to the plough with oxen, which is left on a field, people see two wolves\n"
"(_Volci_) as well. They are the bright stars Sirius in the constellation Canis\n"
"Major and Procyon in Canis Minor."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Hawk
msgid ""
"The Hawk (_Јastreb_), as one of the most famous enemies of the Mother Hen and\n"
"the Rooster, is right above them in an attacking position. Bright star Capella\n"
"(_Kapela_) from the constellation Auriga is actually known among people as\n"
"Hawk."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Cross
msgid ""
"Complement with the people’s belief, when the Priest-thief saw God’s might he\n"
"started running in panic and lost his cross on the way. So next to the Priest’s\n"
"Straw there is the Cross (_Krst_)."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Fox
msgid ""
"Fox (_Lisica_) is the second by importance natural enemy of the Mother Hen and\n"
"the Rooster so it is obvious why people also “see” it on the sky. The red color\n"
"of the bright star Aldebaran from the constellation of the Bull is the reason\n"
"why people perceive it as a Fox ready to attack the Mother Hen and the Rooster."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Tongs
msgid ""
"The Tongs (_Mashi_) were used for the fire where the trivet is. Thus, the\n"
"people’s constellation Tongs is very close to the constellation Trivet."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Ploughman
msgid ""
"The Ploughman (_Orach_) is one of the three main characters in the sky. It is\n"
"the name people gave to the bright star Betelgeuse in the constellation of\n"
"Orion. Besides Betelgeuse, in building the image of this folk constellation,\n"
"some weaker and less bright stars from the surrounding are also taken into\n"
"account, because people say that the Ploughman is an image of a person with a\n"
"goad as he returns home."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Trivet
msgid ""
"The trivet (_Pirustija_) is a metal device with three legs (tripod) which fits\n"
"over the fireplace to support pans and kettles while preparing food."
msgstr ""

# Macedonian constellation, native: софра
msgid "Sofra"
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Sofra
msgid ""
"The typical semi-circular shape of the constellation Corona Borealis evoked the\n"
"image of a wooden round table called _Sofra_."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Pigs
msgid ""
"Near to the Mother Hen, people on the sky noticed the star cluster Hyades.\n"
"Scattered appearance of the stars of this cluster associated people to the\n"
"image of pigs in a village yard, and so it’s called Pigs (_Svinji_)."
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Auger
msgid ""
"Auger (_Svrdel_). People say that this is a very big drill used for\n"
"construction of houses and is found inside the Priest’s Straw."
msgstr ""

# Macedonian constellation, native: уши, pronounce: Ushi
msgid "Ears"
msgstr ""

# Description of Macedonian constellation Ears
msgid ""
"Ears (_Ushi_). By this common word used as a jargon, Macedonian villagers mark\n"
"the part of the wooden plough that goes into the soil, used for plowing."
msgstr ""

